
'''slane'''


==Hiberno-English==

===Noun===


'''slane''' (or [[slean]]) [[Hiberno-English]] word (from the Irish [[sleán]]) -- a spade for cutting [[turf]]. It consists of an iron head and a long wooden shaft. The head has a flat blade, generally with a wing on one side, so that sods can be cut on two sides and detached with a single twist of the implement. There are basically two kinds: the breast slean and the foot slean, with two correspondingly different methods of cutting from the [[turf bank]].